CNCP v1 23410
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#13895:  [script setup] Local variable/computed overrides prop in template with no error/warning",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:16:00.607771+00:00",
  "text": "[script setup] Local variable/computed overrides prop in template with no error/warning\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.2.45\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/jynszh?file=%2Fsrc%2FApp.vue%3A1%2C1-8%2C1\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Define a prop inside <script setup>:\n```\nconst props = defineProps<{ data: number[] }>()\n```\n\n2. Declare a local variable or computed with the same name:\n```\nconst data = computed(() => [...props.data].reverse())\n```\n\n3. Use {{ data }} in the template.\n\n### What is expected?\n\nVue should at least emit a warning/error that a local variable/computed is shadowing a prop.\n\nThis would make the behavior explicit and prevent accidental shadowing bugs.\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\n- No warning or error is emitted.\n\n- In the template, the local variable/computed always takes precedence over the prop.\n\n- Developers may assume they are using the prop, but actually they are using the shadowing variable.\n\n- This is non-obvious and can lead to subtle bugs in larger codebases.\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nThis behavior appears specific to <script setup> and the way scope is compiled.\n\nIt would be very helpful if Vue emitted a warning such as:\n```\n[Vue warn]: Local variable \"data\" is shadowing a prop with the same name.\n```\nThis would make it clear to developers why their template is not using the prop as expected.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: sfc",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
